<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>make it so that the group doesnt look at the pvp switch,</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tempra[CC]">Tempra[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:47 a.m. 28/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> make it so that the group doesnt look at the pvp switch,<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1209" TARGET=_self>Geiger and crew please bring this to the developers attention!</A> (Gray Rage (DB))
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>so a pvp+ person could heal a pvp- person and vice versa as long as tehy are grouped.

<P>All of your points are good and make sense DarkHelm. I actually
<BR>&gt; know of more people currently playing on the Non-PvP servers now
<BR>&gt; that tell me they WILL play +PvP server in Retail. They
<BR>&gt; explained their original decision as just wanting to learn the
<BR>&gt; game first during the month or so of beta then go to battle in
<BR>&gt; retail. Additionally, many of the players starting this phase on
<BR>&gt; the -PvP servers DID want to come to to the +PvP, BUT did not
<BR>&gt; want to start all over again especially with the player wipe
<BR>&gt; comin' up in 2 weeks.
<P>&gt; An additional item I would present is longevity of player
<BR>&gt; loyalties to this game. In the past I have noticed that the
<BR>&gt; majority of OLD time Veteren players on a massvely multiplayer
<BR>&gt; game are +PvPers! The fact is that the game will get monotonous
<BR>&gt; and boring after a time and folks will just plain be lookin' for
<BR>&gt; something else to take their attention.
<P>&gt; Last item: The +PvP switch is a horrible idea. No disrespect to
<BR>&gt; the developers, but they are foolin' themslelves with this one.
<BR>&gt; Check this out:
<P>&gt; 1. +PvP and -PvP together grouping. DOH...no spells can interact
<BR>&gt; between them! A -PvP Cleric will not be able to HEAL a +PvP
<BR>&gt; player. I see the necessity of rule to be sure, but how exactly
<BR>&gt; will this encourage folks to go RED? How will they find folks to
<BR>&gt; group with them? What if a freagin mummy diseases them? What if
<BR>&gt; a nasty snake poisons them and they have 10hps left? How is this
<BR>&gt; condusive to group play? If I played with it set up like this, I
<BR>&gt; would not go red until 50th level! (and I am a hard core
<BR>&gt; rplyer/pker) Surely I would play EQ, but only til' I got bored
<BR>&gt; of waxing monsters.
<P>&gt; 2. There are folks like me that just plain are not sure when to
<BR>&gt; make the switch! The +PvP atmosphere with this type arrangement
<BR>&gt; would make reds VERY rare and of varying levels. Good old
<BR>&gt; fashioned group warfare will NOT exist, basically making +PvP
<BR>&gt; disapeer other than an occasional 1 on 1 kill after some clown
<BR>&gt; is almost dead and another walks up on him seeing an easy kill.
<BR>&gt; (Don't forget how hard it is to get a quick kill, there will be
<BR>&gt; very little 1 on 1 kills where one guy does NOT want to fight.
<BR>&gt; All he has to do is run).
<P>&gt; 3. Guilds will disapeer. What will be the sense of a guild if
<BR>&gt; all you do is login and holler for the folks you have already
<BR>&gt; met in game? Level differences will insure that the older folks
<BR>&gt; don't hang with the younger. In the +PvP server guilds are a
<BR>&gt; forum for us to get together/recruit/organize battles. Guilds
<BR>&gt; like DarkenBane Company will provide a place for folks to go
<BR>&gt; offline to interact with others in a way that -PvP guilds can
<BR>&gt; NEVER hope to compare with. +PvP will find more High and Low
<BR>&gt; level characters interacting as the High level try to help the
<BR>&gt; lower get better to help in battle situations.
<P>&gt; 4. Can anyone explain to me what the languages are for? Because
<BR>&gt; they surely are not used in the -PvP server, but we of the +PvP
<BR>&gt; use them ALL the TiME! the developers implimented a unique and
<BR>&gt; VERY cool comminications system that ONLY the +PvPers use!
<P>&gt; It is my belief that FAILING to have a +PvP server in the final
<BR>&gt; would be a huge mistake. No threats, as I plan to play
<BR>&gt; regardless....but it would definately not meet my expectations
<BR>&gt; of the game if they left it out.
<P>&gt; -Gray
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
